parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure Leading to Vehicle Fires
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to catch fire, resulting in a total loss of the vehicle and potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: flames shoot out from under the hood
electrical short or shock in the ignition switch
wiring harness under the dash shorts out
and the vehicle catches fire in the steering column.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to catch fire, resulting in a total loss of the vehicle and potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Electrical short or shock in the ignition switch
causing the vehicle to catch fire in the steering column

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiring harness can cause the vehicle to catch fire, resulting in a total loss of the vehicle and potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Wiring harness under the dash shorts out
and all wiring had burned completely out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause loss of control, accidents, and leave the driver stranded.
Failure of the TFI ignition module can cause engine stalling, leading to loss of control, accidents, and leaving the driver stranded.
Failure of the fuel system can cause engine stalling, fires, and leave the driver stranded.
Failure of dealerships to properly diagnose and repair issues, and refusal to honor warranties, can lead to frustration, financial loss, and safety risks.
Engine fires can cause damage to the vehicle, injury, and even death.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping or Failure to Engage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or failure to engage can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or roll unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The transmission makes a clicking sound when shifted into gear
the vehicle rolls or moves unexpectedly
the vehicle loses power or stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the drive shaft can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or roll unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: the vehicle rolls or moves unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the axle can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
The malfunction of the shift lever can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The shift lever is stuck or stuck between gears
the vehicle rolls or moves unexpectedly
damage to the vehicle or surrounding property occurs.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel System Electrical Short and Fire Hazard
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical short in the fuel system can cause a fire, which can lead to vehicle damage, injury, or even fatalities.
symptoms: sudden fire in the engine compartment.
